Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (no need to peel).

Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Halfway through, toss the chips with the @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%g} then return to the oven for remaining time.

Meanwhile, cut the @baguettes{2} lengthways down the middle (don't slice all the way through).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @Irish bacon{170%g} until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Keep the bacon fat in the pan and return to medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @passata{1%pack}, @chipotle paste{1%sachet}, @red wine jus{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml}.

> Double both water and sugar quantities for 4p.

Bring to the boil, stirring, then lower the heat slightly and simmer until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, crumble the crispy bacon.

Move the chips to the bottom shelf of the oven.

Pop the baguettes onto a separate lined baking tray.

Spoon as much chilli as you like into each baguette, then top with the @grated cheese{50%g}.

Cook on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese is melted and bubbling, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{120%g}, halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

When everything is almost ready, toss the salad leaves with the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Plate up the chipotle chilli-filled baguettes and sprinkle over the bacon crumble.

Serve the cheesy chips and salad alongside.